2011-07-20T13:43:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/kenya-s-sasini-gains-for-a-second-day-as-coffee-tea-prices-jump.html
Sasini Ltd. (STCL) , a Kenyan tea and coffee
producer, advanced a second day after tea and top-grade coffee
prices increased at an auction yesterday.  The stock climbed 0.5 percent to 10.20 shillings at the
3 p.m. end of trading in Nairobi, the longest winning streak
since May 26.  African tea prices rose for a second week, climbing to an
average of $2.82 per kilogram (2.2 pounds) at a sale in the
Kenyan port city of Mombasa, up from $2.81 a week earlier, Tea
Brokers East Africa Ltd. said in an e-mailed report yesterday.  The price of AA grade Kenyan coffee climbed 5.1 percent at
an auction on lower supplies, the Nairobi Coffee Exchange said
yesterday. It sold for an average $456.59 per 50 kilogram (110
pound) bag, up from $432.24 a week ago.  To contact the reporter on this story:
